This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on developing a deep learning algorithm for object contour detection. Additionally, the paper mentions using PASCAL VOC and MS COCO datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision research.

The paper also involves training a neural network end-to-end, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The use of refined ground truth and inaccurate polygon annotations suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.

The paper's focus on deep learning and neural networks may also suggest that it belongs to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.

Finally, the paper's use of multiscale combinatorial grouping algorithm suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
